#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.117"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.117:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.117:0.2"
msgid "12. Āpāyikavagga "
msgstr "12. Bound for Loss "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.117:0.3"
msgid "117. Vipattisampadāsutta "
msgstr "117. Failures and Accomplishments "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.117:1.1"
msgid "“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, vipattiyo. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are three failures. "

msgctxt "an3.117:1.2"
msgid "Katamā tisso? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.117:1.3"
msgid "Sīlavipatti, cittavipatti, diṭṭhivipatti. "
msgstr "Failure in ethics, mind, and view. "

msgctxt "an3.117:1.4"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sīlavipatti? "
msgstr "And what is failure in ethics? "

msgctxt "an3.117:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when someone kills living creatures, steals, commits sexual misconduct, and uses speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. "

msgctxt "an3.117:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sīlavipatti. "
msgstr "This is called ‘failure in ethics’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.117:2.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, cittavipatti? "
msgstr "And what is failure in mind? "

msgctxt "an3.117:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti byāpannacitto. "
msgstr "It’s when someone is covetous and malicious. "

msgctxt "an3.117:2.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, cittavipatti. "
msgstr "This is called ‘failure in mind’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.269, sc3
msgctxt "an3.117:3.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, diṭṭhivipatti? "
msgstr "And what is failure in view? "

msgctxt "an3.117:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco micchādiṭṭhiko hoti viparītadassano: "
msgstr "It’s when someone has wrong view, a distorted perspective, such as: "

msgctxt "an3.117:3.3"
msgid "‘natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ, natthi hutaṃ, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ, kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko, natthi paro loko, natthi mātā, natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no obligation to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’ "

msgctxt "an3.117:3.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, diṭṭhivipatti. "
msgstr "This is called ‘failure in view’. "

msgctxt "an3.117:3.5"
msgid "Sīlavipattihetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti; "
msgstr "Some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell because of failure in ethics, "

msgctxt "an3.117:3.6"
msgid "cittavipattihetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti; "
msgstr "mind, "

msgctxt "an3.117:3.7"
msgid "diṭṭhivipattihetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti. "
msgstr "or view. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.117:3.8"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso vipattiyoti. "
msgstr "These are the three failures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.117:4.1"
msgid "Tisso imā, bhikkhave, sampadā. "
msgstr "There are three accomplishments. "

msgctxt "an3.117:4.2"
msgid "Katamā tisso? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.117:4.3"
msgid "Sīlasampadā, cittasampadā, diṭṭhisampadā. "
msgstr "Accomplishment in ethics, mind, and view. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.117:5.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sīlasampadā? "
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in ethics? "

msgctxt "an3.117:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when someone doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, or use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. "

msgctxt "an3.117:5.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sīlasampadā. "
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in ethics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.117:6.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, cittasampadā? "
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in mind? "

msgctxt "an3.117:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti abyāpannacitto. "
msgstr "It’s when someone is content and kind-hearted. "

msgctxt "an3.117:6.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, cittasampadā. "
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.270, sc7
msgctxt "an3.117:7.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, diṭṭhisampadā? "
msgstr "And what is accomplishment in view? "

msgctxt "an3.117:7.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sammādiṭṭhiko hoti aviparītadassano: "
msgstr "It’s when someone has right view, an undistorted perspective, such as: "

msgctxt "an3.117:7.3"
msgid "‘atthi dinnaṃ, atthi yiṭṭhaṃ, atthi hutaṃ, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, atthi ayaṃ loko, atthi paro loko, atthi mātā, atthi pitā, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. "
msgstr "‘There is meaning in giving, sacrifice, and offerings. There are fruits and results of good and bad deeds. There is an afterlife. There are obligation to mother and father. There are beings reborn spontaneously. And there are ascetics and brahmins who are well attained and practiced, and who describe the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’ "

msgctxt "an3.117:7.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, diṭṭhisampadā. "
msgstr "This is called accomplishment in view. "

msgctxt "an3.117:7.5"
msgid "Sīlasampadāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; "
msgstr "Some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm because of accomplishment in ethics, "

msgctxt "an3.117:7.6"
msgid "cittasampadāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; "
msgstr "mind, "

msgctxt "an3.117:7.7"
msgid "diṭṭhisampadāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti. "
msgstr "or view. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.117:7.8"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso sampadā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the three accomplishments.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.117:7.9"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

